d procedures and functions with PL/pgSQL\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Functions\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H8_O6v2b0h4}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n-- create a simple function returning integer cents\nCREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION calculate_order_total(item_total integer, tax_percent integer)\nRETURNS integer AS $$\nBEGIN\n  RETURN item_total + ROUND((item_total * tax_percent) / 100.0)::integer;\nEND;\n$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;\n\n-- create a procedure to adjust inventory and record an order\nCREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE process_order(p_order_id integer, p_user_id integer)\nLANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$\nBEGIN\n  -- business logic: lock and check inventory, update tables\n  -- exception handling ensures rollback on errors\n  PERFORM some_inventory_check(p_order_id);\nEXCEPTION WHEN others THEN\n  RAISE NOTICE \'order processing failed for %\', p_order_id;\n  RAISE;\nEND;\n$$;\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// sample order items in cents const items = [300, 400, 200]; // helper to sum array values function sum(arr) { return arr.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0); } // compute subtotal const subtotal = sum(items); // compute tax (10%) rounded const tax = Math.round(subtotal * 0.10); // shipping in cents const shipping = 195; // final total const total = subtotal + tax + shipping; console.log(\"order total \" + total);\n}}\n\n{{answer: order total 1185}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H8_O6v2b0h4',4,15,1,'2026-05-16 19:48:47','2026-05-16 20:18:15',NULL,'javascript'),('1c0584f3-5147-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','1c0561e7-5147-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Create roles, grant privileges, and apply least-privilege principles','code_example',1,'Learn how to create roles, grant granular privileges, and enforce least-privilege access control. This lesson demonstrates role creation, user-role assignment, targeted GRANT/REVOKE commands, and auditing inherited permissions so accounts get only required rights. Youظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظـز╪زll see SQL examples and a simulated starter script to verify effective privileges before deployment. Common pitfall: overprivileging through broad grants or role proliferation.','Lesson: Create roles, grant privileges, and apply least-privilege principles\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security\n\n- https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v18.x/docs/api/crypto.html\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6rY2G3z3qz4}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n-- create roles for least-privilege model\nCREATE ROLE readonly;\nCREATE ROLE teller;\nCREATE ROLE admin;\n\n-- create users (passwords are placeholders)\nCREATE USER alice WITH PASSWORD \'changeme\';\nCREATE USER bob WITH PASSWORD \'changeme\';\nCREATE USER carol WITH PASSWORD \'changeme\';\n\n-- grant table-level privileges to roles\nGRANT SELECT ON TABLE accounts TO readonly;\nGRANT SELECT, UPDATE ON TABLE accounts TO teller;\n\n-- assign roles to users\nGRANT readonly TO alice;\nGRANT teller TO bob;\nGRANT readonly TO carol;\nGRANT teller TO carol;\n\n-- revoke as needed to tighten privileges\nREVOKE UPDATE ON TABLE accounts FROM teller WHERE inappropriate_condition;\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Simulate roles and privileges for the lesson // Create role definitions with allowed actions const roles = { readonly: [\'select\'], teller: [\'select\', \'update\'], admin: [\'select\', \'insert\', \'update\', \'delete\'] }; // Map users to assigned roles const users = { alice: [\'readonly\'], bob: [\'teller\'], carol: [\'readonly\', \'teller\'] }; // Compute effective privileges for a given user function effectivePrivileges(user) { const assigned = users[user] || []; const privSet = new Set(); assigned.forEach(r => { (roles[r] || []).forEach(p => privSet.add(p)); }); return Array.from(privSet).sort().join(\' \'); } // Show carol\'s effective privileges as the lesson verification console.log(effectivePrivileges(\'carol\'));\n}}\n\n{{answer: select update}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6rY2G3z3qz4',1,12,1,'2026-05-16 19:48:47','2026-05-16 20:18:28',NULL,'javascript'),('1c05d771-5147-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','1c0561e7-5147-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Perform logical backups and restores using pg_dump and pg_restore','code_example',1,'Demonstrates how to perform logical backups and restores with pg_dump and pg_restore, including common options and workflows for protecting PostgreSQL data. Youظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظـز╪زll learn when to use custom-format dumps, selective object restores, and restore flags that preserve ownership and extensions. Why: ensures recoverability and portability. Pitfall: relying on defaults can miss object ownership, roles, or extension dependenciesظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥愆氀眀愀礀猀 琀攀猀琀 爀攀猀琀漀爀攀猀 椀渀 愀 猀琀愀最椀渀最 攀渀瘀椀爀漀渀洀攀渀琀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 倀攀爀昀漀爀洀 氀漀最椀挀愀氀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀猀 愀渀搀 爀攀猀琀漀爀攀猀 甀猀椀渀最 瀀最开搀甀洀瀀 愀渀搀 瀀最开爀攀猀琀漀爀攀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䄀倀䤀⼀䌀漀渀猀漀氀攀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀渀漀搀攀樀猀⸀漀爀最⼀愀瀀椀⼀昀猀⸀栀琀洀氀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀䨀瀀　猀嘀㠀瀀㄀爀堀儀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀⌀ 挀爀攀愀琀攀 愀 挀甀猀琀漀洀ⴀ昀漀爀洀愀琀 搀甀洀瀀尀渀瀀最开搀甀洀瀀 ⴀ䘀挀 ⴀ昀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀猀⼀瀀爀漀搀甀挀琀椀漀渀⸀搀甀洀瀀 瀀爀漀搀甀挀琀椀漀渀开搀戀尀渀尀渀⌀ 搀甀洀瀀 猀挀栀攀洀愀 漀渀氀礀尀渀瀀最开搀甀洀瀀 ⴀ猀 ⴀ昀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀猀⼀猀挀栀攀洀愀⸀猀焀氀 瀀爀漀搀甀挀琀椀漀渀开搀戀尀渀尀渀⌀ 爀攀猀琀漀爀攀 椀渀琀漀 愀 渀攀眀 搀愀琀愀戀愀猀攀Ⰰ 挀氀攀愀渀椀渀最 漀戀樀攀挀琀猀 昀椀爀猀琀尀渀挀爀攀愀琀攀搀戀 猀琀愀最椀渀最开搀戀尀渀瀀最开爀攀猀琀漀爀攀 ⴀⴀ挀氀攀愀渀 ⴀⴀ渀漀ⴀ漀眀渀攀爀 ⴀⴀ搀戀渀愀洀攀㴀猀琀愀最椀渀最开搀戀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀猀⼀瀀爀漀搀甀挀琀椀漀渀⸀搀甀洀瀀尀渀怀怀怀尀渀尀渀䰀椀瘀攀 䌀漀搀椀渀最 吀愀猀欀㨀尀渀尀渀刀甀渀 琀栀攀 猀琀愀爀琀攀爀 挀漀搀攀Ⰰ 琀栀攀渀 挀漀洀瀀氀攀琀攀 琀栀攀 吀伀䐀伀猀⸀尀渀尀渀笀笀猀琀愀爀琀攀爀㨀尀渀⼀⼀ 猀椀洀甀氀愀琀攀 愀 氀漀最椀挀愀氀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀 甀猀椀渀最 瀀最开搀甀洀瀀 挀漀渀猀漀氀攀⸀氀漀最⠀尀✀猀琀愀爀琀椀渀最 氀漀最椀挀愀氀 戀愀挀欀甀瀀 甀猀椀渀最 瀀最开搀甀洀瀀尀✀⤀ 挀漀渀猀漀氀攀⸀氀漀最⠀尀✀戀愀挀欀甀瀀 猀愀瘀攀搀 琀漀