爀愀洀攀琀攀爀猀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 甀琀椀氀椀琀礀 最攀渀攀爀椀挀 洀攀琀栀漀搀猀 琀漀 戀甀椀氀搀 挀氀攀愀爀攀爀 䄀倀䤀猀⸀ 圀栀礀㨀 瀀爀攀瘀攀渀琀猀 䌀氀愀猀猀䌀愀猀琀䔀砀挀攀瀀琀椀漀渀 愀渀搀 猀椀洀瀀氀椀昀椀攀猀 挀氀椀攀渀琀 挀漀搀攀⸀ 倀椀琀昀愀氀氀㨀 漀瘀攀爀甀猀椀渀最 爀愀眀 琀礀瀀攀猀Ⰰ 椀渀挀漀爀爀攀挀琀 戀漀甀渀搀猀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀甀爀瀀爀椀猀椀渀最 戀攀栀愀瘀椀漀爀 昀爀漀洀 琀礀瀀攀 攀爀愀猀甀爀攀㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شuse wildcards and proper bounds to maintain flexibility without sacrificing safety.','Lesson: Write generic classes and methods for type-safe APIs\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2b1D5uGm0rI}}\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Simulate Java generic Box<T> concept in JavaScript function Box(value) { this.value = value; } Box.prototype.get = function() { return this.value; }; function pairSwap(a, b) { // generic-like utility that swaps two values return [b, a]; } const stringBox = new Box(\"hello\"); const intBox = new Box(42); // simulate using a generic method and printing both boxed values console.log(\"boxed string \" + stringBox.get() + \" boxed integer \" + intBox.get());\n}}\n\n{{answer: boxed string hello boxed integer 42}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2b1D5uGm0rI',3,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:38:04','2026-05-15 19:38:04',NULL,'javascript'),('725acfb8-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','7259887e-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Process collections with lambda expressions and Streams API','code_example',1,'Use Java-style lambdas and Stream operations to transform and analyze collections. This lesson demonstrates map, filter, reduce and collect patterns using concise functional expressions, explaining when to prefer Streams for readability and parallelization. Learn to avoid common pitfalls: unintended side effects, relying on mutable shared state, and expecting evaluation order with parallel streams. Examples map to Java code patterns and show idiomatic, testable transformations.','Lesson: Process collections with lambda expressions and Streams API\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/reduce\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1YkXgXw6xM}}\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n/* Simulate Java Streams operations with JavaScript arrays (map, filter, reduce, collect) to mirror Java examples. */ const users = [ { name: \'Alice\', age: 23 }, { name: \'bob\', age: 17 }, { name: \'Charlie\', age: 31 }, { name: \'dana\', age: 15 } ]; // map: transform names to uppercase (analogous to stream().map(...)) const namesUpper = users.map(u => u.name.toUpperCase()); // filter + map: select adults and get their names const adultNames = users.filter(u => u.age >= 18).map(u => u.name); // reduce: total age (analogous to stream().reduce(...)) const totalAge = users.reduce((sum, u) => sum + u.age, 0); // collect-like: unique initials (using a Set) const initials = new Set(users.map(u => u.name.charAt(0).toLowerCase())); // Log outputs plainly (lowercase and no punctuation so expected output is deterministic) console.log(namesUpper.join(\' \').toLowerCase()); console.log(adultNames.join(\' \').toLowerCase()); console.log(totalAge.toString()); console.log(Array.from(initials).join(\' \').toLowerCase());\n}}\n\n{{answer: alice bob charlie dana alice charlie 86 a b c d}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1YkXgXw6xM',4,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:38:04','2026-05-15 19:38:04',NULL,'javascript'),('725b4125-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','7259887e-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Read and write files using java.nio.file and serialization','code_example',1,'Learn how to perform file read/write operations with java.nio.file and how to serialize/deserialize objects for simple persistence. This lesson explains writing and reading files, choosing paths, and using Java serialization for object state storage. You\'ll see why persistence matters and common pitfalls such as incompatible serialVersionUID, transient fields, and character-encoding/exception handling when working with file I/O and object streams. Hands-on exercises reinforce safe patterns and error handling.','Lesson: Read and write files using java.nio.file and serialization\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/stringify\n\n- https://nodejs.org/api/fs.html\n\n- https://nodejs.org/api/buffer.html\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1vg0J0dY4Kc}}\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Simulated file write/read and object serialization (browser-safe) const storage = {}; // in-memory fake filesystem const user = { name: \"Alice\", age: 30, active: true }; // serialize and write (equivalent to writing bytes with java.nio.file) storage[\'user.json\'] = JSON.stringify(user); // read and deserialize (equivalent to reading bytes and deserializing an object) const data = JSON.parse(storage[\'user.json\']); // final output shows deserialized values (lowercase, no punctuation to match expected output) console.log(`${data.name.toLowerCase()} ${data.age} ${data.active}`);\n}}\n\n{{answer: alice 30 true}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1vg0J0dY4Kc',5,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:38:04','2026-05-15 19:38:04',NULL,'javascript'),('725c3e21-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','725be7d4-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Create and manage threads using Thread and Runnable','code_example',1,'Implement Runnable or extend Thread to start concurrent tasks and control lifecycle basics using start, run, join, and interrupt. Understand why threads improve responsiveness and parallel CPU utilization, and when to prefer Runnable for composition. Pitfalls: shared mutable state requires synchronization to prevent data races, and careless lifecycle handling can cause leaks or deadlocks. Short examples show safe startup and simple coordination patterns.','Lesson: Create and manage threads using Thread and Runnable\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/EventLoop\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API/Using_web_workers\n\n- https://nodejs.org/api/worker_threads.html\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HVJK9MaD5XI}}\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\nconsole.log(\"main start\"); setTimeout(() => console.log(\"thread a running\"), 0); setTimeout(() => console.log(\"thread b running\"), 0); console.log(\"main end\");\n}}\n\n{{answer: main start main end thread a running thread b running}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HVJK9MaD5XI',1,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:38:05','2026-05-15 19:38:05',NULL,'javascript'),('725cda24-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','725be7d4-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Coordinate concurrency with ExecutorService and synchronization utilities','code_example',1,'Coordinate Java concurrency using ExecutorService, synchronized, Lock, and java.util.concurrent collections like ConcurrentHashMap and CountDownLatch. Learn how ExecutorService thread pools manage task execution and why synchronization and high-level utilities prevent race conditions and deadlocks. Practice patterns for safe shared-state updates, awaiting task completion, and avoiding common pitfalls such as holding locks during I/O or mixing synchronized and lock-based code. Includes a runnable example simulating latch coordination and predictable task ordering.','Lesson: Coordinate concurrency with ExecutorService and synchronization utilities\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fmflXc6f3A0}}\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\nconst latch = { count: 3 }; function task(name, delay) { setTimeout(() => { console.log(`task ${name} done`); latch.count--; if (latch.count === 0) console.log(\'latch reached zero\'); }, delay); } // simulate three tasks submitted to an ExecutorService-like pool task(\'a\', 30); task(\'b\', 60); task(\'c\', 90); // expected behavior: tasks complete in ascending delay order\n}}\n\n{{answer: task a done task b done task c done latch reached zero}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fmflXc6f3A0',2,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:38:05','2026-05-15 19:38:05',NULL,'javascript'),('725d5b79-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','725be7d4-507c-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Build TCP clients and servers with java.net.Socket and ServerSocket','code_example',1,'Build simple TCP clients and servers using java.net.Socket and ServerSocket. Learn how to accept connections, exchange byte/character streams, and design minimal application protocols. This lesson shows why correct resource management, threading for concurrent clients, and buffering strategies matter. Common pitfalls include leaking sockets/streams, blocking accept/read calls without threads, and mishandling character encodings ظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥 愀氀氀 漀昀 眀栀椀挀栀 挀愀渀 栀愀渀最 漀爀 挀漀爀爀甀瀀琀 挀漀洀洀甀渀椀挀愀琀椀漀渀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 䈀甀椀氀搀 吀䌀倀 挀氀椀攀渀琀猀 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀猀 眀椀琀栀 樀愀瘀愀⸀渀攀琀⸀匀漀挀欀攀琀 愀渀搀 匀攀爀瘀攀爀匀漀挀欀攀琀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䄀倀䤀⼀圀攀戀匀漀挀欀攀琀猀开䄀倀䤀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀䜀氀漀猀猀愀爀礀⼀吀䌀倀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀渀漀搀攀樀猀⸀漀爀最⼀愀瀀椀⼀渀攀琀⸀栀琀洀氀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀㌀儀渀䐀㈀挀㐀堀漀瘀欀紀紀尀渀尀渀䰀椀瘀攀 䌀漀搀椀渀最 吀愀猀欀㨀尀渀尀渀刀甀渀 琀栀攀 猀琀愀爀