ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شavoid by adding clearfix or using modern layout alternatives like flexbox or grid.','Lesson: Float elements and clear floats for wrap-around layouts\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/float\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/clear\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/CSS/Block_formatting_context\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RGOj5yH7evk}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<div class=\"wrap clearfix\">\n  <div class=\"thumb\"></div>\n  <p>Text wraps around the float thanks to the clearfix, keeping the container height intact.</p>\n</div>\n\n.thumb { float: left; margin-right: 12px; width: 140px; }\n.clearfix::after { content: \"\"; display: table; clear: both; }\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Inject CSS for demo const css = ` .wrap { width: 640px; border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 12px; margin: 16px auto; } .thumb { float: left; margin-right: 12px; width: 140px; height: 90px; background: linear-gradient(135deg,#9bc,#58a); } .clearfix::after { content: \"\"; display: table; clear: both; } `; const style = document.createElement(\'style\'); style.textContent = css; document.head.appendChild(style); // Create HTML structure with floated element and text that wraps const container = document.createElement(\'div\'); container.className = \'wrap clearfix\'; container.innerHTML = ` <div class=\"thumb\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div> <p>This paragraph demonstrates text wrapping around a floated box. The clearfix class restores the container height so subsequent elements don\'t overlap.</p> `; document.body.appendChild(container); // Indicate success for the lesson quiz console.log(\'clearfix applied\');\n}}\n\n{{answer: clearfix applied}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RGOj5yH7evk',4,15,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f0ac9f-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95ee65d5-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Use CSS units and responsive sizing (px, em, rem, %, vw, vh)','code_example',1,'Learn how to choose and apply CSS unitsظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥瀆砀Ⰰ 攀洀Ⰰ 爀攀洀Ⰰ ─Ⰰ 瘀眀Ⰰ 瘀栀㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شto build scalable, responsive element sizes. This lesson explains when to use absolute vs relative units, how rem and em relate to root and parent font-sizes, and when viewport units or percentages help layout. You\'ll avoid common pitfalls like compounding em calculations and inconsistent root font sizes so designs remain predictable across devices.','Lesson: Use CSS units and responsive sizing (px, em, rem, %, vw, vh)\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/Building_blocks/Values_and_units\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H0XJ_4xw6G0}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<!-- example: mix of units for layout -->\n<style>\n  html { font-size: 16px; }\n  .container { width: 80%; padding: 2rem; }\n  .card { width: 30vw; font-size: 1rem; margin: 1em; }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"card\">rem base, vw width, em margins</div>\n</div>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Set a predictable root font-size document.documentElement.style.fontSize = \'16px\'; // Create a hidden test element that uses rem sizing const box = document.createElement(\'div\'); box.style.width = \'10rem\'; box.style.height = \'50px\'; box.style.position = \'absolute\'; box.style.left = \'-9999px\'; document.body.appendChild(box); // Read computed width and log it const width = getComputedStyle(box).width; console.log(\'box width \' + width);\n}}\n\n{{answer: box width 160px}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H0XJ_4xw6G0',5,12,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f122b5-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95f0f22e-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Apply color using named colors, hex, rgb(), rgba(), and hsl()','code_example',1,'Show how to set and manipulate colors and opacity using named colors, hex, rgb(), rgba(), and hsl() in CSS. Learn when to use each notation, how rgba and hsla provide alpha transparency, and how to convert between formats. Includes a browser-safe starter script that verifies rgba opacity. Pitfall: computed colors may normalize whitespace and rgba formattingظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥愆氀眀愀礀猀 瀀愀爀猀攀 瘀愀氀甀攀猀Ⰰ 渀漀琀 爀愀眀 猀琀爀椀渀最猀Ⰰ 眀栀攀渀 琀攀猀琀椀渀最 瀀爀漀最爀愀洀洀愀琀椀挀愀氀氀礀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 䄀瀀瀀氀礀 挀漀氀漀爀 甀猀椀渀最 渀愀洀攀搀 挀漀氀漀爀猀Ⰰ 栀攀砀Ⰰ 爀最戀⠀⤀Ⰰ 爀最戀愀⠀⤀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 栀猀氀⠀⤀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀挀漀氀漀爀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀挀漀氀漀爀开瘀愀氀甀攀⼀爀最戀愀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀挀漀氀漀爀开瘀愀氀甀攀⼀栀猀氀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀䠀㄀椀堀　瘀　樀䔀夀欀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀⸀渀愀洀攀搀 笀尀渀  戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀㨀 爀攀搀㬀尀渀紀尀渀⸀栀攀砀 笀尀渀  戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀㨀 ⌀昀昀　　　　㬀尀渀紀尀渀⸀爀最戀 笀尀渀  戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀㨀 爀最戀⠀㈀㔀㔀Ⰰ 　Ⰰ 　⤀㬀尀渀紀尀渀⸀爀最戀愀 笀尀渀  戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀㨀 爀最戀愀⠀㈀㔀㔀Ⰰ 　Ⰰ 　Ⰰ 　⸀㔀⤀㬀尀渀紀尀渀⸀栀猀氀 笀尀渀  戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀㨀 栀猀氀⠀　Ⰰ ㄀　　─Ⰰ 㔀　─⤀㬀尀渀紀尀渀怀怀怀尀渀尀渀䰀椀瘀攀 䌀漀搀椀渀最 吀愀猀欀㨀尀渀尀渀刀甀渀 琀栀攀 猀琀愀爀琀攀爀 挀漀搀攀Ⰰ 琀栀攀渀 挀漀洀瀀氀攀琀攀 琀栀攀 吀伀䐀伀猀⸀尀渀尀渀笀笀猀琀愀爀琀攀爀㨀尀渀⼀⨀ 匀琀愀爀琀攀爀 猀挀爀椀瀀琀㨀 挀爀攀愀琀攀猀 愀 栀椀搀搀攀渀 攀氀攀洀攀渀琀Ⰰ 愀瀀瀀氀椀攀猀 爀最戀愀Ⰰ 爀攀愀搀猀 挀漀洀瀀甀琀攀搀 挀漀氀漀爀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 氀漀最猀 爀攀猀甀氀琀 ⨀⼀ 挀漀渀猀琀 攀氀 㴀 搀漀挀甀洀攀渀琀⸀挀爀攀愀琀攀䔀氀攀洀攀渀琀⠀尀✀搀椀瘀尀✀⤀㬀 攀氀⸀猀琀礀氀攀⸀眀椀搀琀栀 㴀 尀✀㄀瀀砀尀✀㬀 攀氀⸀猀琀礀氀攀⸀栀攀椀最栀琀 㴀 尀✀㄀瀀砀尀✀㬀 攀氀⸀猀琀礀氀攀⸀瀀漀猀椀琀椀漀渀 㴀 尀✀愀戀猀漀氀甀琀攀尀✀㬀 攀氀⸀猀琀礀氀攀⸀氀攀昀琀 㴀 尀✀ⴀ㤀㤀㤀㤀瀀砀尀✀㬀 攀氀⸀猀琀礀氀攀⸀戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀䌀漀氀漀爀 㴀 尀✀爀最戀愀⠀㈀㔀㔀Ⰰ　Ⰰ　Ⰰ　⸀㔀⤀尀✀㬀 搀漀挀甀洀攀渀琀⸀戀漀搀礀⸀愀瀀瀀攀渀搀䌀栀椀氀搀⠀攀氀⤀㬀 挀漀渀猀琀 挀漀洀瀀甀琀攀搀 㴀 最攀琀䌀漀洀瀀甀琀攀搀匀琀礀氀攀⠀攀氀⤀⸀戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀䌀漀氀漀爀㬀 ⼀⼀ 洀愀琀挀栀 爀最戀愀 漀爀 爀最戀 愀渀搀 挀愀瀀琀甀爀攀 愀氀瀀栀愀 椀昀 瀀爀攀猀攀渀琀 挀漀渀猀琀 洀 㴀 挀漀洀瀀甀琀攀搀⸀洀愀琀挀栀⠀⼀爀最戀愀㼀