 paragraph, then log computed values document.body.innerHTML = ` <style> body { font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6; padding: 20px; } p { max-width: 60ch; } </style> <p id=\"demo\">This paragraph demonstrates font-size and line-height values used for readability.</p> `; const p = document.getElementById(\'demo\'); const cs = getComputedStyle(p); const fontSize = cs.fontSize; // e.g. \"18px\" const fontSizeValue = parseFloat(fontSize); const lineHeightRaw = cs.lineHeight; // could be \"28.8px\" let lineHeightValue; if (lineHeightRaw.endsWith(\'px\')) { lineHeightValue = (parseFloat(lineHeightRaw) / fontSizeValue).toFixed(1); } else { lineHeightValue = lineHeightRaw; } console.log(`computed font-size ${fontSize} and line-height ${lineHeightValue}`);\n}}\n\n{{answer: computed font-size 18px and line-height 1.6}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3t0Y8QGz2Wk',2,12,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f29ec5-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95f0f22e-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Load and use web fonts with @font-face and Google Fonts','code_example',1,'Learn to integrate web fonts using @font-face and third-party providers like Google Fonts. This lesson shows when to self-host versus linking, how to write @font-face rules, apply font-family in CSS, and use the Font Loading API to reduce layout shift. You\'ll also learn common pitfalls: blocking render, FOUT/FOIT trade-offs, and how font-display and preloading mitigate performance issues. Practical code shows preload, fallbacks, and a small script to detect load state.','Lesson: Load and use web fonts with @font-face and Google Fonts\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FontFaceSet\n\n- https://fonts.google.com/about\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QbWgXwQ7vAY}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<style>\n@font-face {\n  font-family: \"MyLocal\";\n  src: url(\"/fonts/MyLocal.woff2\") format(\"woff2\");\n  font-weight: 400 700;\n  font-display: swap;\n}\nbody {\n  font-family: \"Inter\", \"MyLocal\", system-ui, sans-serif;\n}\n</style>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n/* Wait until the browser reports fonts are ready, then log a message */ document.fonts.ready.then(function() { console.log(\'fonts loaded successfully\'); }).catch(function() { console.log(\'fonts failed to load\'); });\n}}\n\n{{answer: fonts loaded successfully}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QbWgXwQ7vAY',3,15,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f30585-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95f0f22e-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Create backgrounds and gradients with background-image and linear-gradient','code_example',1,'Configure background images and gradients using background-image and linear-gradient to build layered, responsive backgrounds. This lesson teaches positioning, sizing, repeating, and combining multiple background layers for overlays, patterns, and textures. Learn practical techniques for gradient directions, stop points, and repeating-linear-gradient for subtle tiling. Pitfall: layer order and background-size can unintentionally hide layersظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥爆攀洀攀洀戀攀爀 琀栀攀 昀椀爀猀琀 氀椀猀琀攀搀 氀愀礀攀爀 爀攀渀搀攀爀猀 漀渀 琀漀瀀 愀渀搀 琀攀猀琀 搀椀昀昀攀爀攀渀琀 猀椀稀攀猀 琀漀 愀瘀漀椀搀 漀搀搀 琀椀氀椀渀最⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 䌀爀攀愀琀攀 戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀猀 愀渀搀 最爀愀搀椀攀渀琀猀 眀椀琀栀 戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀ⴀ椀洀愀最攀 愀渀搀 氀椀渀攀愀爀ⴀ最爀愀搀椀攀渀琀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀戀愀挀欀最爀漀甀渀搀ⴀ椀洀愀最攀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀氀椀渀攀愀爀ⴀ最爀愀搀椀攀渀琀尀渀尀渀