 functions: clamp(), min(), max(), and fit-content()\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/clamp\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/fit-content\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6o7g3G8i9jM}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<!-- HTML structure -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"clamped\">clamp example</div>\n  <div class=\"mined\">min example</div>\n  <div class=\"maxed\">max example</div>\n  <div class=\"fit\">fit-content example</div>\n</div>\n\n/* CSS */\n.container { width: 800px; }\n.clamped { width: clamp(100px, 50%, 200px); }\n.mined   { width: min(60%, 250px); }\n.maxed   { width: max(20%, 180px); }\n.fit     { width: fit-content(300px); padding: 8px; }\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Simulate a fixed layout context so computed results are deterministic const containerWidth = 800; // px // clamp(100px, 50%, 200px) -> clamp between 100 and 200, 50% of container is 400 const clampResult = Math.min(Math.max(100, 0.5 * containerWidth), 200); // 200 // min(60%, 250px) -> min of 480 and 250 const minResult = Math.min(0.6 * containerWidth, 250); // 250 // max(20%, 180px) -> max of 160 and 180 const maxResult = Math.max(0.2 * containerWidth, 180); // 180 // Simulated fit-content: intrinsic content width versus a limit const contentWidth = 100; // px intrinsic content const fitContentResult = Math.min(contentWidth, 300); // 100 // Log a single predictable, lowercase, no punctuation string console.log(\"clamp \" + clampResult + \"px min \" + minResult + \"px max \" + maxResult + \"px fit content \" + fitContentResult + \"px\");\n}}\n\n{{answer: clamp 200px min 250px max 180px fit content 100px}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6o7g3G8i9jM',5,12,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f9624c-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95f75512-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Animate UI with transitions and transforms','code_example',1,'Learn to add smooth state changes and motion with CSS transitions and 2D/3D transforms. This lesson shows when to use transitions vs transforms, how to chain effects, and how to combine translate/scale/rotate with perspective for depth. You\'ll also learn performance best practices like animating transform and opacity, using will-change, and avoiding layout-triggering properties to prevent jank. Cover timing functions, easing, transition shorthand, and respecting user motion preferences.','Lesson: Animate UI with transitions and transforms\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transform\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/will-change\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7c0a6gG4V0o}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<div class=\"card\">Hover or click me</div>\n\n.card {\n  width: 200px;\n  height: 120px;\n  background: coral;\n  transition: transform 300ms ease, box-shadow 300ms ease;\n  transform-origin: center;\n}\n.card:hover { transform: translateY(-10px) rotateX(6deg) scale(1.03); box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.2); }\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Insert CSS for a simple card that animates on the active class const style = document.createElement(\'style\'); style.textContent = ` .card { width: 220px; height: 120px; margin: 40px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: linear-gradient(135deg,#ff9a9e,#fad0c4); border-radius: 12px; transition: transform 300ms cubic-bezier(.2,.9,.2,1), box-shadow 300ms ease; transform-origin: center; will-change: transform, box-shadow; cursor: pointer; } .card.active { transform: translateY(-14px) rotateX(6deg) scale(1.04); box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.18); } `; document.head.appendChild(style); // Create the interactive element const card = document.createElement(\'div\'); card.className = \'card\'; card.textContent = \'click to animate\'; document.body.appendChild(card); // Toggle animation state card.addEventListener(\'click\', () => { card.classList.toggle(\'active\'); }); // Log when the transform transition completes for the quiz card.addEventListener(\'transitionend\', (e) => { if (e.propertyName === \'transform\') { console.log(\'animation complete\'); } });\n}}\n\n{{answer: animation complete}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7c0a6gG4V0o',1,15,0,'2026-05-15 20:22:01','2026-05-15 20:22:01',NULL,'javascript'),('95f9e6da-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','95f75512-5082-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Create keyframe animations and control timing','code_example',1,'Show how to define @keyframes and apply animations to elements, and explain controlling duration, easing, delay, and iteration to produce expressive motion. Learn why precise timing matters for perceived performance and accessibility, and how staggered delays create rhythm. Pitfall: overly long or abrupt timing can feel sluggish or jarring and repeated animations can harm performance ظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥 琀攀猀琀 眀椀琀栀 爀攀搀甀挀攀搀ⴀ洀漀琀椀漀渀 甀猀攀爀猀 愀渀搀 氀椀洀椀琀 栀攀愀瘀礀Ⰰ 挀漀渀琀椀渀甀漀甀猀 愀渀椀洀愀琀椀漀渀猀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 䌀爀攀愀琀攀 欀攀礀昀爀愀洀攀 愀渀椀洀愀琀椀漀渀猀 愀渀搀 挀漀渀琀爀漀氀 琀椀洀椀渀最尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀䀀欀攀礀昀爀愀洀攀猀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀愀渀椀洀愀琀椀漀渀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䌀匀匀⼀愀渀椀洀愀琀椀漀渀ⴀ琀椀洀椀渀最ⴀ昀甀渀挀琀椀漀渀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀䔀搀猀砀昀开一䈀䘀爀眀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀㰀搀椀瘀 挀氀愀猀猀㴀尀∀戀漀砀尀∀㸀㰀⼀搀椀瘀㸀尀渀尀渀⸀戀漀砀 笀尀渀  眀椀搀琀栀㨀 ㄀㈀　瀀砀㬀尀渀  栀攀椀最栀琀㨀 ㄀㈀　瀀砀㬀尀渀  愀渀椀洀愀琀椀