椀攀渀琀ⴀ猀椀搀攀 挀栀攀挀欀猀㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شalways validate on the server as well.','Lesson: Perform client-side form validation and manage submission with JavaScript\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Form_validation\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3PHXvlpOkf4}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n// submit handler snippet (core idea)\nform.addEventListener(\'submit\', function(event) {\n  event.preventDefault();\n\nif (!validateForm(form)) return; // stop if invalid\n\n// on valid data, proceed (e.g., send to server)\n  console.log(\'form submitted\');\n});\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// create a simple form dynamically so this runs standalone const form = document.createElement(\'form\'); form.id = \'signupForm\'; const nameInput = document.createElement(\'input\'); nameInput.name = \'name\'; nameInput.required = true; nameInput.placeholder = \'Full name\'; form.appendChild(nameInput); const emailInput = document.createElement(\'input\'); emailInput.name = \'email\'; emailInput.type = \'email\'; emailInput.required = true; emailInput.placeholder = \'Email\'; form.appendChild(emailInput); const submitBtn = document.createElement(\'button\'); submitBtn.type = \'submit\'; submitBtn.textContent = \'Submit\'; form.appendChild(submitBtn); document.body.appendChild(form); // simple validation helper function validateForm(form) { const name = form.elements[\'name\'].value.trim(); const email = form.elements[\'email\'].value.trim(); const emailValid = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/.test(email); return name.length > 0 && emailValid; } // submit handler: prevent submission on invalid data and log on success form.addEventListener(\'submit\', function(event) { event.preventDefault(); if (!validateForm(form)) { // lightweight feedback: use browser\'s validity interface form.elements[\'email\'].setCustomValidity(\'\'); if (!form.elements[\'email\'].checkValidity()) { form.elements[\'email\'].setCustomValidity(\'invalid\'); } return; // do not proceed when invalid } // success path (could send fetch here) console.log(\'form submitted\'); }); // preset valid values and programmatically submit to demonstrate the flow form.elements[\'name\'].value = \'Alice\'; form.elements[\'email\'].value = \'alice@example.com\'; form.requestSubmit();\n}}\n\n{{answer: form submitted}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3PHXvlpOkf4',5,15,0,'2026-05-16 17:22:56','2026-05-16 17:22:56',NULL,'javascript'),('bbd618a2-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','bbd5ee54-5132-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Work with callbacks, Promises, and async/await to handle asynchronous code','code_example',1,'Learn to convert callback-based APIs into Promises and async/await for clearer asynchronous flows. This lesson shows why Promises improve error handling and composition, demonstrates a simple promisify pattern, then uses async/await for sequential logic. You\'ll practice preserving execution order and avoiding callback hell. Pitfall: promisifying without proper error handling can hide rejections ظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥 愀氀眀愀礀猀 昀漀爀眀愀爀搀 攀爀爀漀爀猀 愀渀搀 爀攀樀攀挀琀 眀栀攀渀 挀愀氀氀戀愀挀欀猀 猀椀最渀愀氀 昀愀椀氀甀爀攀 愀渀搀 搀攀戀甀最最椀渀最 猀琀爀愀琀攀最椀攀猀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 圀漀爀欀 眀椀琀栀 挀愀氀氀戀愀挀欀猀Ⰰ 倀爀漀洀椀猀攀猀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 愀猀礀渀挀⼀愀眀愀椀琀 琀漀 栀愀渀搀氀攀 愀猀礀渀挀栀爀漀渀漀甀猀 挀漀搀攀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀䜀氀漀猀猀愀爀礀⼀䌀愀氀氀戀愀挀欀开昀甀渀挀琀椀漀渀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀⼀䜀甀椀搀攀⼀唀猀椀渀最开瀀爀漀洀椀猀攀猀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀⼀刀攀昀攀爀攀渀挀攀⼀匀琀愀琀攀洀攀渀琀猀⼀愀猀礀渀挀开昀甀渀挀琀椀漀渀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀嘀开䬀爀㤀伀匀昀䐀攀唀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀⼀⼀ 瀀爀漀洀椀猀椀昀礀 瀀愀琀琀攀爀渀 攀