㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شalways test across DPRs and viewports.','Lesson: Use picture and srcset to deliver responsive images\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/picture\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img#attr-srcset\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img#attr-sizes\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H8uF9YQ2ZKs}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<picture>\n  <source\n    type=\"image/webp\"\n    srcset=\"hero-800w.webp 800w, hero-1600w.webp 1600w, hero-3200w.webp 3200w\"\n    sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 50vw\">\n  <source\n    srcset=\"hero-800w.jpg 800w, hero-1600w.jpg 1600w, hero-3200w.jpg 3200w\"\n    sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 50vw\">\n  <img src=\"hero-1600w.jpg\" alt=\"Hero image showing product\">\n</picture>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\nconst srcset = [ { url: \'hero-800w.jpg\', w: 800 }, { url: \'hero-1600w.jpg\', w: 1600 }, { url: \'hero-3200w.jpg\', w: 3200 } ]; function chooseFor(dpr, cssWidth) { const needed = dpr * cssWidth; // device pixel ratio times CSS display width let chosen = srcset[srcset.length - 1]; for (const c of srcset) { if (c.w >= needed) { chosen = c; break; } } // normalize to a simple lowercase label without punctuation for this lesson\'s output return chosen.url.replace(/\\./g, \' \').replace(/-/g, \' \').toLowerCase(); } // Assume a device pixel ratio of 2 and a CSS display width of 800px console.log(chooseFor(2, 800));\n}}\n\n{{answer: hero 1600w jpg}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H8uF9YQ2ZKs',3,12,0,'2026-05-15 19:47:33','2026-05-15 19:47:33',NULL,'javascript'),('c5281185-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','c526ac8d-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Optimize images with attributes (alt, width/height, loading=\'lazy\')','code_example',1,'Learn to optimize images by adding descriptive alt text, explicit width and height attributes, and native lazy loading. This lesson explains what each attribute does, why specifying dimensions prevents layout shifts and improves CLS, and how lazy loading defers offscreen images to speed page load. Beware: incorrect widths can distort images and redundant or empty alt text harms accessibilityظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥昆漀氀氀漀眀 猀椀稀攀Ⰰ 愀猀瀀攀挀琀 爀愀琀椀漀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 洀攀愀渀椀渀最昀甀氀 愀氀琀 琀攀砀琀 戀攀猀琀 瀀爀愀挀琀椀挀攀猀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 伀瀀琀椀洀椀稀攀 椀洀愀最攀猀 眀椀琀栀 愀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀 ⠀愀氀琀Ⰰ 眀椀搀琀栀⼀栀攀椀最栀琀Ⰰ 氀漀愀搀椀渀最㴀尀✀氀愀稀礀尀✀⤀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀倀攀爀昀漀爀洀愀渀挀攀⼀䰀愀稀礀开氀漀愀搀椀渀最尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀䰀攀愀爀渀⼀䠀吀䴀䰀⼀䴀甀氀琀椀洀攀搀椀愀开愀渀搀开攀洀戀攀搀搀椀渀最⼀刀攀猀瀀漀渀猀椀瘀攀开椀洀愀最攀猀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀㌀眀　䨀㌀焀夀　戀匀䔀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀㰀℀ⴀⴀ 䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀 䠀吀䴀䰀 猀栀漀眀椀渀最 漀瀀琀椀洀椀稀攀搀 椀洀愀最攀 愀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀 ⴀⴀ㸀尀渀㰀椀洀最尀渀  猀爀挀㴀尀∀瀀栀漀琀漀⸀樀瀀最尀∀尀渀  愀氀琀㴀尀∀洀漀甀渀琀愀椀渀 猀甀渀爀椀猀攀尀∀尀渀  眀椀搀琀栀㴀尀∀㠀　　尀∀尀渀  栀攀椀最栀琀㴀尀∀㘀　　尀∀尀渀  氀漀愀搀椀渀最㴀尀∀氀愀稀礀尀∀尀渀㸀尀渀㰀℀ⴀⴀ 匀瀀攀挀椀昀礀 爀攀愀氀 椀渀琀爀椀渀猀椀挀 椀洀愀最攀 猀椀稀攀猀 琀漀 愀瘀漀椀搀 氀愀礀漀甀琀 猀栀椀昀琀猀 愀渀搀 甀猀攀 洀攀愀渀椀渀最昀甀氀 愀氀琀 琀攀砀琀 ⴀⴀ㸀尀渀怀怀怀尀渀尀渀䰀椀瘀攀 䌀漀搀椀渀最 吀愀猀欀㨀尀渀尀渀刀甀渀 琀栀攀 猀琀愀爀琀攀爀 挀漀搀攀Ⰰ 琀栀攀渀 挀漀洀瀀氀攀琀攀 琀栀攀 吀伀䐀伀猀⸀尀渀尀渀笀笀猀琀愀爀琀攀爀㨀尀渀⼀⼀ 吀栀椀猀 猀挀爀椀瀀琀 挀爀攀愀琀攀猀 愀渀 椀洀愀最攀 攀氀攀洀攀渀琀Ⰰ 猀攀琀猀 挀漀洀洀漀渀 漀瀀琀椀洀椀稀愀琀椀漀渀 愀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀Ⰰ ⼀⼀ 愀渀搀 瀀爀椀渀琀猀 愀 猀椀渀最氀攀ⴀ氀椀渀攀 猀甀洀洀愀爀礀 琀漀 琀栀攀 挀漀渀猀漀氀攀⸀ 挀漀渀猀琀 椀洀最 㴀 搀漀挀甀洀攀渀琀⸀挀爀攀愀琀攀䔀氀攀洀攀渀琀⠀尀✀椀洀最尀✀⤀㬀 椀洀最⸀猀爀挀 㴀 尀✀瀀栀漀琀漀⸀樀瀀最尀✀㬀 椀洀最⸀愀氀琀 㴀 尀✀洀漀甀渀琀愀椀渀 猀甀渀爀椀猀攀尀✀㬀 椀洀最⸀眀椀搀琀栀 㴀 㠀　　㬀 椀洀最⸀栀攀椀最栀琀 㴀 㘀　　㬀 椀洀最⸀氀漀愀搀椀渀最 㴀 尀✀氀愀稀礀尀✀㬀 挀漀渀猀琀 漀甀琀瀀甀琀 㴀 怀愀氀琀 ␀笀椀洀最⸀愀氀琀紀 眀椀搀琀栀 ␀笀椀洀最⸀眀椀搀琀栀紀 栀攀椀最栀琀 ␀笀椀洀最⸀栀攀椀最栀琀紀 氀漀愀搀椀渀最 ␀笀椀洀最⸀氀漀愀搀椀渀最紀怀㬀 挀漀渀猀漀氀攀⸀氀漀最⠀漀甀琀瀀甀琀⤀㬀尀渀紀紀尀渀尀渀笀笀愀渀猀眀攀爀㨀 愀氀琀 洀漀甀渀琀愀椀渀 猀甀渀爀椀猀攀 眀椀搀琀栀 㠀　　 栀攀椀最栀琀 㘀　　 氀漀愀搀椀渀最 氀愀稀礀紀紀✀Ⰰ✀栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀㌀眀　䨀㌀焀夀　戀匀䔀✀Ⰰ㐀Ⰰ㄀㔀Ⰰ　Ⰰ✀㈀　㈀㘀ⴀ　㔀ⴀ㄀㔀 ㄀㤀㨀㐀㜀㨀㌀㌀✀Ⰰ✀㈀　㈀㘀ⴀ　㔀ⴀ㄀㔀 ㄀㤀㨀㐀㜀㨀㌀㌀✀Ⰰ一唀䰀䰀Ⰰ✀樀愀瘀愀猀挀爀椀瀀琀✀⤀Ⰰ⠀✀挀㔀㈀㠀㤀㤀㈀㘀ⴀ㔀　㜀搀ⴀ㄀㄀昀㄀ⴀ㤀愀戀攀ⴀ㘀挀　㈀攀　搀㈀㘀㠀㈀㄀✀Ⰰ✀挀㔀㈀㘀愀挀㠀搀ⴀ㔀　㜀搀ⴀ㄀㄀昀㄀ⴀ㤀愀戀攀ⴀ㘀挀　㈀攀　搀㈀㘀㠀㈀㄀✀Ⰰ✀䰀椀渀欀 愀渀搀 瀀爀攀氀漀愀搀 爀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀 眀椀琀栀 氀椀渀欀Ⰰ 猀挀爀椀瀀琀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 爀攀氀 愀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀✀Ⰰ✀挀漀搀攀开攀砀愀洀瀀氀攀✀Ⰰ㄀Ⰰ✀䰀攀愀爀渀 琀漀 椀渀挀氀甀搀攀 愀渀搀 栀椀渀琀 爀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀 氀漀愀搀椀渀最 甀猀椀渀最 氀椀渀欀 爀攀氀 瘀愀氀甀攀猀 ⠀瀀爀攀氀漀愀搀Ⰰ 瀀爀攀昀攀琀挀栀Ⰰ 猀琀礀氀攀猀栀攀攀琀⤀ 愀渀搀 猀挀爀椀瀀琀 愀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀 ⠀搀攀昀攀爀Ⰰ 愀猀礀渀挀⤀⸀ 吀栀椀猀 氀攀猀猀漀渀 攀砀瀀氀愀椀渀猀 眀栀攀渀 愀渀搀 眀栀礀 琀漀 甀猀攀 攀愀挀栀 栀椀渀琀 琀漀 椀洀瀀爀漀瘀攀 瀀攀爀昀漀爀洀愀渀挀攀Ⰰ 栀漀眀 琀漀 猀攀琀 愀猀⼀琀礀瀀攀 挀漀爀爀攀挀琀氀礀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 戀攀猀琀 瀀爀愀挀琀椀挀攀猀 昀漀爀 猀挀爀椀瀀琀 瀀氀愀挀攀洀攀渀琀⸀ 倀椀琀昀愀氀氀㨀 椀渀挀漀爀爀攀挀琀 愀猀 瘀愀氀甀攀猀Ⰰ 爀攀搀甀渀搀愀渀琀 瀀爀攀氀漀愀搀猀Ⰰ 漀爀 漀瘀攀爀甀猀椀渀最 愀猀礀渀挀⼀搀攀昀攀爀 挀愀渀 戀爀攀愀欀 攀砀攀挀甀琀椀漀渀 漀爀搀攀爀 漀爀 眀愀猀琀攀 戀愀渀搀眀椀搀琀栀㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شuse hints sparingly for critical assets only.','Lesson: Link and preload resources with link, script, and rel attributes\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Link_types/preload\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/script\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3cH1cBq8mvs}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <!-- hint the browser to fetch a critical stylesheet early -->\n  <link rel=\"preload\" href=\"/css/styles.css\" as=\"style\">\n  <!-- hint for probable next navigation -->\n  <link rel=\"prefetch\" href=\"/js/next-page.js\">\n  <!-- place non-blocking scripts in head with defer -->\n  <script src=\"/js/lib.js\" defer></script>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <!-- critical inline script remains blocking if necessary -->\n  <script>\n    console.log(\'critical inline behavior\');\n  </script>\n  <script src=\"/js/app.js\" defer></script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\nconsole.log(\'preload hint applied\'); console.log(\'inline script executed\'); setTimeout(() => { console.log(\'deferred script executed\'); }, 0); if (document.readyState === \'loading\') { document.addEventListener(\'DOMContentLoaded\', () => { console.log(\'dom content loaded\'); }); } else { console.log(\'dom content loaded\'); }\n}}\n\n{{answer: preload hint applied inline script executed dom content loaded deferred script executed}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3cH1cBq8mvs',5,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:47:33','2026-05-15 19:47:33',NULL,'javascript'),('c52908c9-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','c528e565-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Create form controls: text, password, checkbox, radio, select, textarea','code_example',1,'Assemble common HTML form controls ظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥 琀攀砀琀Ⰰ 瀀愀猀猀眀漀爀搀Ⰰ 挀栀攀挀欀戀漀砀Ⰰ 爀愀搀椀漀Ⰰ 猀攀氀攀挀琀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 琀攀砀琀愀爀攀愀 㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪ش and learn when each is appropriate. Why: choosing the right control improves user experience, semantics, and data quality. Pitfall: missing name attributes, poor label associations, or mismatched types break accessibility and submissions; also rely on server-side validation since client-side checks can be bypassed.','Lesson: Create form controls: text, password, checkbox, radio, select, textarea\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Introduction_to_forms\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/How_to_structure_a_web_form_for_accessibility\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<form>\n  <label>Name: <input type=\"text\" name=\"name\"></label>\n  <label>Password: <input type=\"password\" name=\"password\"></label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"newsletter\"> Subscribe</label>\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Gender</legend>\n    <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"gender\" value=\"female\"> Female</label>\n    <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"gender\" value=\"male\"> Male</label>\n  </fieldset>\n  <label>Color:\n    <select name=\"color\">\n      <option value=\"red\">Red</option>\n      <option value=\"green\">Green</option>\n    </select>\n  </label>\n  <label>Comments: <textarea name=\"comments\"></textarea></label>\n</form>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// build form const formHtml = ` <form id=\"demoForm\"> <label> Name <input name=\"name\" type=\"text\" value=\"alice\"></label> <label> Password <input name=\"password\" type=\"password\" value=\"secret\"></label> <label> Newsletter <input name=\"newsletter\" type=\"checkbox\" checked></label> <fieldset> <legend>Gender</legend> <label><input name=\"gender\" type=\"radio\" value=\"female\" checked> Female</label> <label><input name=\"gender\" type=\"radio\" value=\"male\"> Male</label> </fieldset> <label>Color <select name=\"color\"> <option value=\"red\">Red</option> <option value=\"green\" selected>Green</option> </select> </label> <label>Comments <textarea name=\"comments\">hello</textarea> </label> <button type=\"submit\">Send</button> </form> `; document.body.innerHTML = formHtml; document.getElementById(\'demoForm\').addEventListener(\'submit\', function(e) { e.preventDefault(); const f = e.target; const data = { name: f.name.value, password: f.password.value, newsletter: f.newsletter.checked ? \'checked\' : \'unchecked\', gender: f.gender.value, color: f.color.value, comments: f.comments.value.trim() }; console.log(`form submitted name ${data.name} password ${data.password} newsletter ${data.newsletter} gender ${data.gender} color ${data.color} comments ${data.comments}`); }); document.getElementById(\'demoForm\').requestSubmit();\n}}\n\n{{answer: form submitted name alice password secret newsletter checked gender female color green comments hello}}',NULL,1,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:47:33','2026-05-15 19:47:33',NULL,'javascript'),('c5296959-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','c528e565-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Use semantic input types (email, url, number, date) for improved UX','code_example',1,'Choose semantic input typesظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥攆洀愀椀氀Ⰰ 甀爀氀Ⰰ 渀甀洀戀攀爀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 搀愀琀攀㠀䀆㈆㠆䀆䀆㠆숆¤ش┬胂㠀숆¤ش╪شto enable native keyboards, pickers, and built-in validation that improve accessibility and mobile UX. This lesson shows practical selection criteria, HTML patterns, and a live example that leverages browser constraints. Learn common pitfalls: browsersظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظـز╪ز validations are helpful but inconsistent, so combine semantic types with explicit checks and friendly messages to avoid false security assumptions or poor cross-browser behavior.','Lesson: Use semantic input types (email, url, number, date) for improved UX\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#attr-type\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Form_validation\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<form id=\"contact\">\n  <label>Email: <input type=\"email\" name=\"email\" required></label>\n  <label>Website: <input type=\"url\" name=\"website\" required></label>\n  <label>Age: <input type=\"number\" name=\"age\" min=\"1\" max=\"120\" required></label>\n  <label>Appointment: <input type=\"date\" name=\"appointment\" required></label>\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Insert a small form with semantic input types and set valid values document.body.innerHTML = ` <form id=\"contact\"> <label>Email: <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" required></label> <label>Website: <input type=\"url\" id=\"site\" required></label> <label>Age: <input type=\"number\" id=\"age\" min=\"1\" max=\"120\" required></label> <label>Appointment: <input type=\"date\" id=\"appt\" required></label> </form> `; const form = document.getElementById(\'contact\'); // Populate with valid example values document.getElementById(\'email\').value = \'user@example.com\'; document.getElementById(\'site\').value = \'https://example.com\'; document.getElementById(\'age\').value = \'30\'; document.getElementById(\'appt\').value = \'2025-01-01\'; // Use the browser\'s built-in validity check if (form.checkValidity()) { console.log(\'form valid\'); } else { console.log(\'form invalid\'); }\n}}\n\n{{answer: form valid}}',NULL,2,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:47:33','2026-05-15 19:47:33',NULL,'javascript'),('c529c04f-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','c528e565-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Build accessible forms: associate labels, legends, placeholders, and tabindex','code_example',1,'Show how to make forms navigable and understandable by associating label elements with inputs, grouping related fields with fieldset and legend, providing helpful placeholders, and controlling tab order with tabindex. Learn why explicit labels improve screen-reader semantics and how groupings communicate structure. Pitfall: using placeholders as sole labels or non-sequential tabindex values that break predictable keyboard navigation.','Lesson: Build accessible forms: associate labels, legends, placeholders, and tabindex\n\n> Note: Live JavaScript editor runs in the browser. Avoid `require`, `process`, and server startup code here.\n\nUseful Resources:\n\n- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/tabindex\n\n{{video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8t0DLm1T2iI}}\n\nExample:\n\n```code\n<form>\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Contact info</legend>\n    <label for=\"name\">Full name</label>\n    <input id=\"name\" name=\"name\" placeholder=\"Jane Doe\" tabindex=\"1\">\n    <label>Email\n      <input type=\"email\" name=\"email\" placeholder=\"you@example.com\" tabindex=\"2\">\n    </label>\n    <button type=\"submit\" tabindex=\"3\">Send</button>\n  </fieldset>\n</form>\n```\n\nLive Coding Task:\n\nRun the starter code, then complete the TODOs.\n\n{{starter:\n// Insert an accessible form into the page and count focusable elements const formHtml = ` <form id=\"contact\"> <fieldset> <legend>Contact information</legend> <label for=\"name\">Full name</label> <input id=\"name\" name=\"name\" placeholder=\"Jane Doe\" tabindex=\"1\"> <label>Email <input type=\"email\" name=\"email\" placeholder=\"you@example.com\" tabindex=\"2\"> </label> <label for=\"subscribe\">Subscribe</label> <input id=\"subscribe\" type=\"checkbox\" name=\"subscribe\" tabindex=\"3\"> <label for=\"message\">Message</label> <textarea id=\"message\" name=\"message\" placeholder=\"Your message\" tabindex=\"4\"></textarea> <button type=\"submit\" tabindex=\"5\">Send</button> </fieldset> </form> `; document.body.innerHTML = formHtml; const focusable = document.querySelectorAll( \'a[href], button, input, textarea, select, [tabindex]:not([tabindex=\"-1\"])\' ); console.log(\'focusable elements \' + focusable.length);\n}}\n\n{{answer: focusable elements 5}}','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8t0DLm1T2iI',3,15,0,'2026-05-15 19:47:33','2026-05-15 19:47:33',NULL,'javascript'),('c52a2951-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','c528e565-507d-11f1-9abe-6c02e0d26821','Implement client-side validation with required, pattern, minlength, and maxlength','code_example',1,'This lesson demonstrates using HTML validation attributes required, pattern, minlength, and maxlength to enforce input constraints before form submission. You will learn practical attribute usage, crafting patterns for common formats, and combining length limits for better UX. Why: reduces invalid submissions and gives immediate feedback. Pitfall: client-side checks are convenient but can be bypassed ظـزظــظ꓂㐀Ⰶ숥ظ꓂㐀樆㐥 愀氀眀愀礀猀 瘀愀氀椀搀愀琀攀 漀渀 琀栀攀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 愀渀搀 琀攀猀琀 攀搀最攀ⴀ挀愀猀攀 瀀愀琀琀攀爀渀猀⸀✀Ⰰ✀䰀攀猀猀漀渀㨀 䤀洀瀀氀攀洀攀渀琀 挀氀椀攀渀琀ⴀ猀椀搀攀 瘀愀氀椀搀愀琀椀漀渀 眀椀琀栀 爀攀焀甀椀爀攀搀Ⰰ 瀀愀琀琀攀爀渀Ⰰ 洀椀渀氀攀渀最琀栀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 洀愀砀氀攀渀最琀栀尀渀尀渀㸀 一漀琀攀㨀 䰀椀瘀攀 䨀愀瘀愀匀挀爀椀瀀琀 攀搀椀琀漀爀 爀甀渀猀 椀渀 琀栀攀 戀爀漀眀猀攀爀⸀ 䄀瘀漀椀搀 怀爀攀焀甀椀爀攀怀Ⰰ 怀瀀爀漀挀攀猀猀怀Ⰰ 愀渀搀 猀攀爀瘀攀爀 猀琀愀爀琀甀瀀 挀漀搀攀 栀攀爀攀⸀尀渀尀渀唀猀攀昀甀氀 刀攀猀漀甀爀挀攀猀㨀尀渀尀渀ⴀ 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀搀攀瘀攀氀漀瀀攀爀⸀洀漀稀椀氀氀愀⸀漀爀最⼀攀渀ⴀ唀匀⼀搀漀挀猀⼀圀攀戀⼀䠀吀䴀䰀⼀䄀琀琀爀椀戀甀琀攀猀⼀瀀愀琀琀攀爀渀尀渀尀渀笀笀瘀椀搀攀漀㨀 栀琀琀瀀猀㨀⼀⼀眀眀眀⸀礀漀甀琀甀戀攀⸀挀漀洀⼀眀愀琀挀栀㼀瘀㴀㌀礀搀瘀㜀瀀㤀琀䜀瘀䤀紀紀尀渀尀渀䔀砀愀洀瀀氀攀㨀尀渀尀渀怀怀怀挀漀搀攀尀渀㰀昀漀爀洀 椀搀㴀尀∀猀椀最渀甀瀀尀∀㸀尀渀  㰀氀愀戀攀氀㸀尀渀    唀猀攀爀渀愀洀攀尀渀    㰀椀渀瀀甀琀 渀愀洀攀㴀尀∀甀猀攀爀渀愀洀攀尀∀ 爀攀焀甀椀爀攀搀 洀椀渀氀攀渀最琀栀㴀尀∀㌀尀∀ 洀愀砀氀攀渀最琀栀㴀尀∀㄀㔀尀∀㸀尀渀  㰀⼀氀愀戀攀氀㸀尀渀尀渀㰀氀愀戀攀氀㸀尀渀    䔀洀愀椀氀尀渀  